Final Answer:

Three U.S. national parks outside Ohio that are UNESCO World Heritage Sites, along with nearby commercial airports and flight durations from John Glenn International Airport (CMH):

1. Yellowstone National Park (Wyoming, Montana, Idaho)
   Nearby airport: Bozeman Yellowstone International Airport (BZN)
   Flight duration: Approximately 5 hours 16 minutes (connecting flight)

2. Everglades National Park (Florida)
   Nearby airport: Miami International Airport (MIA)
   Flight duration: Approximately 2 hours 40 minutes (direct flight)

3. Olympic National Park (Washington)
   Nearby airport: Seattle-Tacoma International Airport (SEA)
   Flight duration: Approximately 5 hours 24 minutes (connecting flight)

